<TITLE> India, US say agree nuclear sites, defence pact </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELH, Jul 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India and the United States on Monday said they had agreed on a defence pact that takes a big step toward the sale of sophisticated U.S. arms to India, and on which sites will be reserved for US companies to build two nuclear power plants. Indian External Affairs Minister S.M. Krishna and U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton announced both agreements at a joint press conference at the conclusion of Clinton's first trip to India as Washington's top diplomat.
